From: Debian PHP Maintainers <pkg-php-maint@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2015 10:26:51 +0200
Subject: php-5.4.9-phpinfo

Drop "Configure Command" from phpinfo as it doesn't
provide any useful information.
The available extensions are not related to this command.
---
 ext/standard/info.c                               | 3 ---
 ext/standard/tests/general_functions/phpinfo.phpt | 1 -
 2 files changed, 4 deletions(-)

Index: Local/ext/standard/info.c
===================================================================
--- Local.orig/ext/standard/info.c
+++ Local/ext/standard/info.c
@@ -870,9 +870,6 @@ PHPAPI void php_print_info(int flag)
 #ifdef ARCHITECTURE
 		php_info_print_table_row(2, "Architecture", ARCHITECTURE);
 #endif
-#ifdef CONFIGURE_COMMAND
-		php_info_print_table_row(2, "Configure Command", CONFIGURE_COMMAND );
-#endif
 
 		if (sapi_module.pretty_name) {
 			php_info_print_table_row(2, "Server API", sapi_module.pretty_name );
Index: Local/ext/standard/tests/general_functions/phpinfo.phpt
===================================================================
--- Local.orig/ext/standard/tests/general_functions/phpinfo.phpt
+++ Local/ext/standard/tests/general_functions/phpinfo.phpt
@@ -20,7 +20,6 @@ PHP Version => %s
 
 System => %s
 Build Date => %s%a
-Configure Command => %s
 Server API => Command Line Interface
 Virtual Directory Support => %s
 Configuration File (php.ini) Path => %s
